<node CREATED="1576216631435" ID="ID_10139139" MODIFIED="1576216631435" TEXT="EC2 Backup Method 1: EBS Snapshots. One way to back up EC2 instances is by creating a snapshot of the Elastic Block Storage (EBS) volume or volumes that your EC2 instance uses. EBS snapshots allow you to save the state of an EBS volume at a given point in time then restore it later. This approach to EC2 backup is relatively straightforward." />
</node>
